<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>You Learned: File Magic Numbers</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/learn.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="learn-page">
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="learn-logo">

    <div class="learn-hero">
      <div class="hero-icon">🔮</div>
      <h1>Challenge 6 Complete!</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">The Mystery File</p>
      <div class="flag-badge"><%= flag %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-grid">
      <div class="learn-card skill-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔍</div>
        <h2>Skill Unlocked</h2>
        <h3>File Signature Analysis</h3>
        <p>File extensions are just labels — they can be faked. "Magic numbers" (the first bytes) reveal a file's true type: <code>%PDF</code>, <code>PK</code> (ZIP), <code>89 PNG</code>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card world-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🌍</div>
        <h2>Real World</h2>
        <h3>Malware Disguise</h3>
        <p>Criminals rename viruses from <code>.exe</code> to <code>.pdf</code> to trick people. Antivirus software checks magic numbers rather than trusting extensions — and now you know why.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card career-card">
        <div class="card-icon">👩‍💻</div>
        <h2>Career Path</h2>
        <h3>Malware Analyst</h3>
        <p>Malware analysts examine suspicious files using hex editors and forensic tools. The cybersecurity workforce gap exceeds 3.4 million globally — the field needs you!</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card key-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔑</div>
        <h2>Key Takeaway</h2>
        <h3>Don't Trust Extensions</h3>
        <p>Always verify file types by examining their contents. A <code>.dat</code> file might be a PDF, a <code>.jpg</code> might be a ZIP. Trust the bytes, not the name.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Special completion banner for final challenge -->
    <div class="completion-banner">
      <div class="completion-stars">🏆</div>
      <h2>All 6 Challenges Complete!</h2>
      <p>You explored web security and digital forensics techniques used by real professionals every day.</p>
      <p class="completion-cta">The cybersecurity field needs more women. You could be one of them.</p>
      <p class="completion-sig">— EECS Girls Who Tech Camp</p>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-nav">
      <a href="/" class="nav-btn primary">← Back to All Challenges</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
